r\\\\'s requested task.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor each tool that is relevant to the user\\\\'s prompt, you must generate a policy object.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Output Format\\\\\\\\nYou must return a JSON object with a \\\\\\\\\\\"policies\\\\\\\\\\\" key, which is an array of objects. Each object must have:\\\\\\\\n- \\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\": The name of the tool.\\\\\\\\n- \\\\\\\\\\\"policy\\\\\\\\\\\": An object with:\\\\\\\\n  - \\\\\\\\\\\"permissions\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"allow\\\\\\\\\\\" | \\\\\\\\\\\"deny\\\\\\\\\\\" | \\\\\\\\\\\"ask_user\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n  - \\\\\\\\\\\"constraints\\\\\\\\\\\": A detailed description of conditions (e.g. allowed files, arguments).\\\\\\\\n  - \\\\\\\\\\\"rationale\\\\\\\\\\\": Explanation for the policy.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nExample JSON:\\\\\\\\n```json\\\\\\\\n{\\\\\\\\n  \\\\\\\\\\\"policies\\\\\\\\\\\": [\\\\\\\\n    {\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"read_file\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\"policy\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\"permissions\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"allow\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\"constraints\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"Only allow reading \\\\'main.py\\\\'.\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\"rationale\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"User asked to read main.py\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n      }\\\\\\\\n    },\\\\\\\\n    {\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\"tool_name\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"run_shell_command\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\"policy\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\"permissions\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"deny\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\"constraints\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"None\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n        \\\\\\\\\\\"rationale\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"Shell commands are not needed for this task\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n      }\\\\\\\\n    }\\\\\\\\n  ]\\\\\\\\n}\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n### Guiding Principles:\\\\\\\\n1.  **Permissions:**\\\\\\\\n    *   **allow:** Required tools for the task.\\\\\\\\n    *   **deny:** Tools clearly outside the scope.\\\\\\\\n    *   **ask_user:** Destructive actions or ambiguity.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n2.  **Constraints:**\\\\\\\\n    *   Be specific! Restrict file paths, command arguments, etc.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n3.  **Rationale:**\\\\\\\\n    *   Reference the user\\\\'s prompt.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUser Prompt: \\\\\\\\\\\"You are Gemini CLI acting as the researcher/tester in a 3-agent team.\\\\\\\\nClaude Code is the orchestrator. Codex CLI is the primary executor.\\\\\\\\nAlways plan before executing. Prefer evidence, validation, and reproducible findings.\\\\\\\\nReturn concise markdown with sections: Summary, Findings, Evidence, Commands, Risks, Recommended Handoff.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTask:\\\\\\\\nRound 2 parallel review for task-04 on branch `kpi` of `/home/aiagent/assistant/git/history-production/`. PARALLEL (other reviewer concurrent).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nGEMINI SPECIFIC: STEP 1 = write_file to `/home/aiagent/assistant/git/history-production/reviews/task-04/gemini-round-2.md`. Inline in response if write fails. Do NOT summarise-only.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## r1 verdict = request changes (Codex 3 MED + Gemini 2 MED = 5 union findings)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## What changed in commit 00dff11 (diff: `git diff e277fa7..00dff11 -- .`)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n- **Gemini MED: deletion-blind classifier** \\u2192 _iter_commits uses `git log --raw`, `_active_files` filter. New regression test_deleted_file_does_not_count_as_revision.\\\\\\\\n- **Codex MED: batch phase3 skipped script_started** \\u2192 event_value=\\\\'also:script_started\\\\' set on dual-milestone commits. New test_batch_phase3_commit_flags_also_script_started.\\\\\\\\n- **Codex MED: scaffold regex too broad** \\u2192 anchored `^(scaffold|Initial commit|chore(...):scaffold)`. Confidence ladder 0.9/0.7/0.5. New test_scaffold_regex_rejects_false_positive.\\\\\\\\n- **Codex MED: missing first-city scaffold** \\u2192 second pass upgrades earliest city-touching commit to scaffold conf 0.6 + event_value=\\\\'inferred-first-city\\\\'. New test_no_scaffold_inferred_from_first_city_touch.\\\\\\\\n- **Gemini MED: canonical_path silent drift** \\u2192 SELECT + WARNING log in write_events.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTest suite 82 \\u2192 86. All green.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## Your r2 checklist\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n1. Deletion handling: does `--raw` status parsing correctly handle rename (R) and copy (C) with similarity scores (R100)? New files via `A`?\\\\\\\\n2. Batch-phase3 event_value=\\\\'also:script_started\\\\' \\u2014 is this the right data-model extension, or should it be a separate GitEvent row?\\\\\\\\n3. Scaffold regex: `^(scaffold|Initial commit|chore(?:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\([^)]+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\))?:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\s*scaffold)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\b` \\u2014 does it correctly anchor to subject start? Any legitimate commit subject it would wrongly reject?\\\\\\\\n4. Confidence ladder 0.9/0.7/0.5 for scaffold \\u2014 does it align with task spec\\\\'s classification rigour?\\\\\\\\n5. 2nd-pass first-city-scaffold upgrade: only upgrades if event_type is \\\\'unclassified\\\\' or \\\\'revision\\\\'. What if the earliest event is \\\\'script_started\\\\'? Should that be excluded from upgrade too?\\\\\\\\n6. canonical_path warning: uses _LOG.warning. Does this propagate correctly in production cron context (task-08 runs) where logging may be captured?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n## Output format same as r1\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWrite to `reviews/task-04/{codex|gemini}-round-2.md`. If clean \\u2192 accepted.\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTrusted Tools (Context):\\\\\\\\n[\\\\\\\\n  {\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"update_topic\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"Manages your narrative flow. Include `title` and `summary` only when starting a new Chapter (logical phase) or shifting strategic intent.\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n    \\\\\\\\\\\"parametersJsonSchema\\\\\\\\\\\": {\\\\\\\\n      \\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\\\\\"object\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\n      \\\\