rectly anchored to the start of the subject and uses a word boundary to prevent over-matching. It successfully rejects the false positives from r1, as confirmed by the new `test_scaffold_regex_rejects_false_positive`.\\n\\n4.  **Confidence ladder:** **PASS.** The new three-tiered confidence ladder for scaffolds (0.9 for subject + README, 0.7 for subject + any city file, 0.5 for subject only) is a logical refinement over the original spec. It provides a more granular and accurate representation of evidence strength and aligns with the spirit of the r1 feedback.\\n\\n5.  **2nd-pass first-city-scaffold upgrade:** **PASS.** The logic correctly limits the upgrade to `unclassified` or `revision` event types. Excluding higher-confidence, more specific events like `script_started` is the correct behavior, as it would otherwise result in a loss of information and confidence (demoting a 0.85 `script_started` to a 0.6 `inferred-scaffold`).\\n\\n6.  **`canonical_path` warning:** **PASS.** The implementation correctly uses `_LOG.warning` to flag a potential data drift in `canonical_path`. While visibility of this warning depends on the production cron's logging configuration (which is outside this code's scope), the code itself does the right thing by emitting a standard warning.\\n\\n### New Risks or Regressions\\n\\n-   None identified. The new tests (`test_deleted_file_does_not_count_as_revision`, `test_batch_phase3_commit_flags_also_script_started`, etc.) provide good coverage for the fixes.\\n\\n### Recommended Handoff\\n\\n-   None. The task is complete and can be merged.\",\n+  \"stats\": {\n+    \"models\": {\n+      \"gemini-2.5-pro\": {\n+        \"api\": {\n+          \"totalRequests\": 6,\n+          \"totalErrors\": 0,\n+          \"totalLatencyMs\": 87161\n+        },\n+        \"tokens\": {\n+          \"input\": 59428,\n+          \"prompt\": 142882,\n+          \"candidates\": 1933,\n+          \"total\": 150401,\n+          \"cached\": 83454,\n+          \"thou